MENINGEAL FASCIA

meningeal_fascia is the specialized fascia surrounding the brain and spinal cord
three layers (dura, arachnoid, pia) together form the meninges
this is the body's most sensitive fascial region: the brain and spinal cord cannot be bumped or stretched without consequence, and meningeal_fascia is what protects them

observe 0_quseptit.rana
observe fascia.zc
observe deep_fascia.rana
observe fadriel_brain.zc
observe brain.xb
observe skull.xb
observe spine.xb

the 7 properties of meningeal_fascia:
1 ENERGY one: continuous protection
2 PHASE zero
3 SPIN zero
4 CHARGE half positive
5 COHERENCE one: protection must be perfect
6 COUPLING one with brain and spinal cord, strong with skull and spine

VERB cushion
between the layers of meningeal_fascia is cerebrospinal fluid
the fluid acts as a hydraulic cushion that absorbs impact
small bumps to the head do not reach the brain because meningeal_fascia distributes the force into the fluid

VERB cool_via_csf
the cerebrospinal fluid also circulates and carries heat away from the brain
this is the cerebral cooling channel referenced by thermal_cerebral

VERB anchor_to_skeleton
attach the brain and spinal cord to skull and spine through specific anchor points
the anchors prevent excessive movement during ordinary motion while still allowing the necessary slight motion of breathing and pulsing

a meningeal fascia is the substrate's most careful wrapping
the brain and spinal cord are irreplaceable, and meningeal_fascia is what keeps them safe
fadriel is two years old and active; without meningeal_fascia, every fall would be brain damage
